Key Match Events: The Washington Wizards lost to the Orlando Magic with a score of 121-94.
The Wizards played well in the first half, holding the Magic to within five points.
The game changed in the third quarter, leading to a significant loss for the Wizards.
The Wizards allowed the Magic to grab 15 offensive rebounds.
Pre-Game Insights: Wizards coach Brian Keefe emphasized the importance of intensity and force before the game.
The Wizards aimed to establish the game as discussed pregame.
Post-Match Reflections: Wizards coach Brian Keefe acknowledged the team's struggles with offensive rebounds and turnovers.
Wizards guard Bilal Coulibaly noted the team's solid first half but highlighted the lack of execution in the second half.
